title.narrative: Enhancing water efficiency and food security through Egyptian TVETs

description.narrative:
**Project plan**
This project intends to enhance water efficiency and food security in Egypt by means of capacity building at TVET/HE's and fits perfectly in OKP’s priority themes for Egypt:
- water, linked to food and nutrition security (FNS)
- efficient water management for climate smart agriculture (CSA)
The short version is: setting up thematic workgroups around identified issues in the Delta and at the edge of the Desert, combine Dutch and Egyptian expertise, involving people at TVET/HE like institutions and other stakeholders in an inclusive way, striving for tangible and applicable outputs and disseminate these to farmers, small enterprises, agro-industries and exporters
This is not a research project, but testing of ideas and good practices from elsewhere, before dissemination the outputs in Egypt. A workshop on methodology for developing and implementing participative learning packages will be held, to be able to implement already four learning packages (containing the messages formulated by the working groups) during 2019 and start dissemination through TVET like organizations to the target groups as soon as possible.
Each learning package is prepared by a literature review and include placements, surveys and assignments on the respective topics by joint Dutch and Egyptian workgroups, in which also TVET/HE teachers and students participate; thus attaining problem-based interdisciplinary research and teaching skills, teamwork and further professional development.

comment.narrative: 22-07-2021: 9 topics have been selected in which curricula will be developed: - Protected Cultivation and Climate Smart Agriculture; - On-farm irrigation and drainage, substrates and plant-nutrition management; - Quality improvement and on-farm post-harvest handling; - Irrigation & drainage: using water smartly; - Salinity issues and salt-resistant crops; - Food and post-harvest losses policies; - Value chains & exportability; - Gender and equality in agriculture; - Agricultural export potential and problems to export to the EU. Some of these topics will allow for the development of multiple courses/workshops.

30-04-2020: The process has been started for several other curricula. Research in the themes of water; climate smart agriculture; and food security, value chain and export potential has been conducted as part of this process
